  <brief_title>Role of Skin Cleansing and Prophylactic Antibiotic in Preventing Infectious Morbidity After Cesarean Section Delivery</brief_title>
  <official_title>Role of Skin Cleansing and Prophylactic Antibiotic in Preventing Infectious Morbidity After Cesarean Section Delivery</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Raghda Gamal Mohamed</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Minia Maternity University Hospital</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study aims to determine the effectiveness of skin cleansing and prophylactic antibiotics
      given to women undergoing a cesarean section for reducing the incidence of postpartum
      infectious morbidity and to assess potential maternal adverse effects and any impact on the
      infant.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <overall_status>Not yet recruiting</overall_status>
  <start_date>January 2017</start_date>
